# MediGuard UI — Design Lock

When generating or editing UI, **follow this system** unless the user explicitly requests a redesign.

## Brand & tone

- Product name: **MediGuard AI** (wordmark: MediGuard + AI accent).
- Voice: professional health-tech, calm, trustworthy — **all user-facing copy in English**.
- Not clinical alarmist; include disclaimer that product is not medical advice where relevant.

## Color tokens (match `app/globals.css`)

| Token | Hex | Usage |
|-------|-----|--------|
| background | `#f8fafc` | Page bg |
| foreground | `#0f172a` | Headings, primary text |
| muted | `#64748b` | Secondary text |
| accent | `#0d9488` | CTAs, links, logo mark |
| accent-soft | `#ccfbf1` | Soft highlights, icon bg |
| card | `#ffffff` | Cards, header |
| border | `#e2e8f0` | Dividers |

## Typography

- Sans: **Inter** (`--font-sans`) — UI, marketing.
- Mono: **JetBrains Mono** (`--font-mono`) — code, API paths, JSON.

## Logo & brand assets

- Use `BrandLogo` from `components/brand-logo.tsx` and paths in `lib/jalur-brand.ts`.
- Raster files live in `public/brand/` (source exports may sit in `asset/` at repo root).
- Do not swap to shields, pills, crosses, or gradients on the mark.

## Layout patterns

- Max content width: `max-w-6xl`, horizontal padding `px-6`.
- Header: sticky, `border-b`, `bg-card/80 backdrop-blur-md`.
- Cards: `rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card shadow-soft`.
- Primary button: `rounded-xl bg-accent` white text; secondary: `border border-border bg-card`.
- Sections: generous vertical rhythm (`py-20`), subtle radial hero gradient using `accent-soft`.

## Components (reuse, extend — do not duplicate styles)

- `components/layout-header.tsx`
- `components/section-hero.tsx`
- `components/section-features.tsx`
- `components/panel-database-status.tsx`
- `components/layout-footer.tsx`

## Imagery

- Prefer flat/minimal illustrations; teal + slate palette only.
- Raster brand files: see `design/CHATGPT-ASSET-PROMPTS.md` and `design/brand/README.md`.

## Forbidden UI drift

- Dark hacker aesthetic, neon purple, busy glassmorphism, or new logo shapes.
- Indonesian in UI strings (code comments for new vars may stay Indonesian per repo rules).
